goals.question: What is the range of values for the 'u' coordinate?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the minimum, maximum, median, and outliers of the 'u' coordinate, giving an idea of the spread of the data.

goals.question: What is the correlation between 'u' and 'v' coordinates?
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between the 'u' and 'v' coordinates, indicating if there is any correlation between them.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the 'v' coordinate?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the frequency distribution of the 'v' coordinate, giving an idea of the most common values and the spread of the data.

goals.question: What is the standard deviation of the 'u' coordinate?
goals.rationale: An error bar chart will show the mean and standard deviation of the 'u' coordinate, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the 'u' and 'v' coordinates over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of 'u' and 'v' over time

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['u'])
    plt.title("What is the range of values for the 'u' coordinate?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the correlation between 'u' and 'v' coordinates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='u', y='v', data=data, ci='sd', capsize=0.1)
    plt.title("What is the standard deviation of the 'u' coordinate?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
